<h3>Research</h3>
I started in July 2010 as a Marie Curie postdoc in the <a 
href="http://www2.warwick.ac.uk/fac/sci/maths/research/interests/number_theory/">
Number Theory</a> research group.
<p>
<b>Papers</b>
<ul>
<li>(With P. Bruin, A. Dujella, and F. Najman) 
<i>Ranks of elliptic curves with prescribed torsion over number fields</i>, 
prerpint, <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1201.0252">arXiv link</a>
<li><i>Modular forms applied to the computational inverse Galois problem</i>, 
preprint, submitted, <a href="papers/polynomials.pdf">pdf</a>
<li><i>Computations with modular forms and Galois representations</i>, 
in: Computational aspects of modular forms and Galois representations 
(J-M. Couveignes, S.J. Edixhoven eds.), Ann. Math. Stud. <b>176</b> (2011) 129-157,
 <a href=http://arxiv.org/abs/math/0605244>arXiv link</a>
<li><i>Polynomials for projective representations of level one forms</i>, 
in loc.&#8201;cit., 159-172.
<li><i>Explicit computations with modular Galois representations</i>, 
PhD thesis, Universiteit Leiden, 2008,
<a href=http://hdl.handle.net/1887/13364>link</a>
<li><i>A polynomial with Galois group SL<sub>2</sub>(F<sub>16</sub>)</i>, 
LMS J. Comput. Math. 10 (2007) 378-388, 
<a href="papers/sl2f16.pdf">pdf</a>
<li><i>Boyd's conjecture for a family of genus 2 curves</i>, 
Master's thesis, Universiteit Utrecht, 2004, 
<a href="papers/scriptie.pdf">pdf</a>
<li>(With L. Taelman) <i>On sums of sums of values of Dirichlet characters</i>, 
Nieuw Arch. Wiskd. (5) 2 (2001)  no. 2,  133-134,
<a href="papers/bosman.pdf">pdf</a>
</ul>
<p>
<b>Code</b>
<ul>
Some Magma code that I wrote to compute polynomials and that I included as an appendix to my 
SL<sub>2</sub>(F<sub>16</sub>)-paper can be found <a href="modrep.m">here</a>.  I've made a <a href="poster.pdf">poster</a> that
explains how the code should be used.  I also wrote some <a href="modular_representation.sage">Sage code</a>
that does similar things.
</ul>
